<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-21T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-21T12:00:00-05:00" n="67" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d67">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.5151/184: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-21T14:00:00-03:00">October 21, 1933—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 21—12:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>98. Letter received today from Fred Kent regarding French negotiations in
                            regard to blocked milreis would indicate that he has not been kept
                            informed of reports sent to the Department. Inasmuch as our own milreis
                            agreement may shortly run into acute difficulties, suggest Kent be
                            brought fully up to date.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>